CommonFields.Title: Effect of nanoclay content and compatibilizer on viscoelastic properties of montmorillonite/polypropylene nanocomposites
Author: Venkatesh, G.S.
Deb, A.
Karmarkar, Ajay
Chauhan, Shakti S.
CommonFields.Location: Center for Product Design and Manufacturing, Indian Institute of Science, Bangalore, India

ChooseParameter.Other: m-TMI was absorbed on porous polypropylene granules
mixture was fed through main hopper of the extruder at 50 g/min using a volumetric feeder
Dicumyl peroxide (DCP) was introduced through the side feeder

The temperature of the feed zone, the mixing zone, the reacting zone, and the die zone were set at 180, 190, 200 and 180 C, respectively. Once the heating profile was reached the extrusion was performed
The system started with pure PP and peroxide feed rate was gradually increased to the set value.
After about 10 mins, steady state conditions were achieved and the pure PP feed was changed to mixture of PP and m-TMI

Cooling.Description: The extrudate was cooled on a moving steel belt

Matrix.Description: . m-Isopropenyl-a-a-dimethylbenzyl-isocyanate (m-TMI) was grafted onto PP so that the resulting m-TMI-g-PP could be used as a compatibilizer

Filler.Description: The filler was a natural montmorillonite modified with quaternary ammonium salt

Mixing.Description: a combination of 27.5 g of PP granules and 2.5 g of m-TMI-g-PP were added to mixing chamber

ChooseParameter.Other: 30 g of oven-dried nanoclay was then added to the mixing chamber

Cooling.Description: After mixing, the blend was cooled to rt

ChooseParameter.Other: Resulting mixture (masterbatch) was palletized into approximately 3 mm sized pallets

Mixing.Description: Appropriate amount of masterbatch and pure PP were dry blended

Cooling.Description: the extrudate recovered from the twin-screw extruder was guided into a standard cold water stranding bath

ChooseParameter.Other: cooled strands were chopped into pellets
After drying, the strands were stored in sealed plastic bags

MoldingInfo.Description: molded into standard ASTM D638-94b and ASTM D790-92 type specimens using a microprocessor controlled 60 tonne LT Demag

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Description: dynamic strain (+/-) 1 mm to (+/-) 1.5 mm, static strain up to 35 mm and frequency range of 0.01 to 100 Hz

data.description: Storage Modulus v Temperature at a frequency of 5 Hz
Loss Modulus v Temperature measured at a frequency of 5 Hz

SampleSize.description: sample size used in DMA were 50 mm X 4 mm X 3 mm
